sec.p:
Based on the amount of data in FAMSBASE in 2001 and the amount of increase in the following years, a due year for whole proteome 3D structure models is estimated. Estimation is done residue-wise, not ORF-wise, since modeled structures in FAMSBASE are often limited to structural domains. In this report, structural domains refer to SCOP domains (Andreeva et al. 2004). All ORFs predicted out of genome sequences are divided into soluble and membrane proteins. The division is carried out by SOSUI (Hirokawa et al. 1998), and a protein with one or more transmembrane regions is classified into a membrane protein. The number of residues of whole soluble proteins encoded in the genome sequence (G) of species i is denoted as S\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
